{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (signed, 0 blocking, 10 advisory + 4 overflow). Triage + design decisions (all advisory; resolved here):\n- [E2 fcc12 contract shape] DECIDED: kernel verification contract = Verification{index:int, severity_attributes: SeverityAttrs{prod_impact,debt_impact (none|low|medium|high), blast_radius (local|module|system), likelihood (low|medium|high), reversibility (easy|moderate|hard)}, binary: Binary{cited_reference_accurate (yes|no|insufficient|na = the VETO), + the 7 GRADED_BINARY sub-questions (yes|no|insufficient)}}. Moved verbatim from passes._pass2_model → kernel; registered as 'verification' (single source); plan_review_verification registers the SAME model factory (alias).\n- [E2 f812c arg shapes] DECIDED: verify_findings(findings: list[dict], *, context: str (plan text/diff), run_chunk: Callable[[instructions:str, context:str], dict], window_tokens:int, est_tokens:Callable, headroom:float). The per-gate verify-prompt PREAMBLE is the prompt file (workflow shell), not a kernel arg; context is a plain string.\n- [F1 fc911 degrade assertions] DECIDED: degrade test asserts that when run_chunk raises (unparseable turn after retries), the chunk's findings get NO verification → verify_findings omits their indices → pass3_decide(None) → INDETERMINATE (never crash). Kernel test exercises this.\n- [F1 fb2c3 / E1 f6e92 golden + removal] DECIDED: parity = the existing offline workflow test (test_plan_review_workflow) asserts the verdict partition unchanged; PLUS a new kernel test asserts verify_findings reproduces the engine's merge-by-index output; PLUS a re-export-identity test (contract/listing/chunker ARE the kernel objects) proves no second copy remains.\n- [E1 f5c39 veto vs 7] CLARIFIED: cited_reference_accurate is the conditional VETO (in Binary, value 'na' when no citation), separate from the 7 graded sub-questions used for validity. Documented in the kernel.\n- [T4 f8731 rollback] JUSTIFIED N/A: in-process refactor, no runtime flag; rollback=git revert; the byte-equal-verdict parity test guards the merge so a regression cannot land.\n- [T2 fbb48 chunking generality] ADDRESSED: kernel chunker test covers the multi-chunk boundary + merge-by-GLOBAL-index correctness (a >1-chunk case + the omitted-too-big case), validating the chunking carries over.\n- [T7 f23949 / T5e fee8e docs/ADR] DEFERRED to WS4 (epic's kernel consumer-seam + doc deliverable); WS2 adds kernel module docstrings recording the verification contract + verify_findings API."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782609054306491001,"uuid":"4eb1c359-2274-4601-adcf-1c7599c9b7d5"}